Brasil Foods Co-Chairman Says He Doesn’t Think Buffett Preparing Takeover

-- B y   F r a n c i s c o   M a r c e l i n o
-- 
2011-04-29T16:47:48Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-29/brasil-foods-says-doesn-t-believe-buffett-preparing-takeover.html
Warren Buffett ’s  Berkshire Hathaway
Inc. (BRK/A)  probably isn’t preparing a takeover of meat producer BRF
 Brasil Foods  SA, BRF’s co-chairman said.  “I don’t believe that such a big investor like him is
preparing a takeover of Brasil Foods,” co-chairman Luiz Fernando Furlan said today in an interview in  Rio de Janeiro .  Brazilian newspaper  Valor Economico  reported Feb. 18 that
Berkshire Hathaway began buying shares in the company after
representatives visited Brasil Foods units.  Brasil Foods rose 30 centavos, or 1 percent, to 31.93 reais
as of 1:40 p.m. in Sao Paulo trading.  To contact the reporters on this story:
Francisco Marcelino in Sao Paulo at   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Dale Crofts at   dcrofts@bloomberg.net . 